Even if you pass three objects to the constructor, you&#39;ll always have to pay a single write operation.

On the other hand, if you need to update multiple fields within the same document, then you should pass those values to the [DocumentReference#update()][1] method, as explained in the official documentation:

* https://firebase.google.com/docs/firestore/manage-data/add-data#update_fields_in_nested_objects

P.S. Remember that a batch write is useful only when you want to perform operations at multiple different locations.

